message.content:
Below is a concise breakdown of how the target model is built and which dictionary pieces match each part exactly (without re‐orienting any blocks). 

1)  Description of Main Target Image  
• Total Blocks & Layers:  
  – There are 8 total blocks arranged in 3 layers.  
• Bottom Layer (3 blocks):  
  – A green rectangular prism at the left/front.  
  – An orange triangular wedge directly behind that green block.  
  – A tall orange cylinder on the right.  
• Second Layer (2 blocks):  
  – A blue cube and a yellow cube side‐by‐side on top of the green block.  
  – A large red “C‐shaped” block bridging across the top of the cylinder and partially over the cubes.  
• Top Layer (2 blocks):  
  – Two identical yellow half‐cylinders placed side‐by‐side on top of the red “C‐block.”  

2)  Required Blocks and Their Indices  
• Orange cylinder: index 7  
• Green rectangular prism: index 5  
• Yellow cube: index 4  
• Blue cube: index 3  
• Orange wedge: index 16  
• Red “C‐shaped” block: index 2  
• Two yellow half‐cylinders: index 8 (used twice)  

3)  Assembly Order  
{  
  Step1: Move block with index 5  
  Step2: Move block with index 16  
  Step3: Move block with index 7  
  Step4: Move block with index 3  
  Step5: Move block with index 4  
  Step6: Move block with index 2  
  Step7: Move block with index 8  
  Step8: Move block with index 8  
}
